    "body": "@hello2mao Could you please provide the output of Remix' console after the transaction has failed? This most likely happened because you ran out of gas. On a fresh Remix session using Javascript VM and an initial gas limit of 3000000, ``case_20000`` uses too much gas already. Remix has an analysis feature that warns about infinite gas costs:\r\n\r\n_Gas requirement of function Test.case_20000() high: infinite. If the gas requirement of a function is higher than the block gas limit, it cannot be executed. Please avoid loops in your functions or actions that modify large areas of storage (this includes clearing or copying arrays in storage)_\r\n\r\nDoes this answer your question?\r\n",
